cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with the design of a secure communication protocol for 5G HetNets, which involves wireless networks and security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses cryptographic algorithms and security resilience, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.IT (Information Theory). The proposed scheme involves software-defined wireless networks, which could place it under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
